  <my:Hazards>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="1">
      <my:Description>Slip, trip, fall</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>3</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Adequate illumination to be provided, use portable light if necessary; 
b) Any opening in the unit, covers, access doors to be mounted back as soon as possible; 
c) Tools, screws, parts should be kept in tidy manner, not dropped all around the working area.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="2">
      <my:Description>Improper tools handling</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>2</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>4</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Consult `Operating Handheld Powered Tools `Risk Assessment when using such tools; 
b) Consult &#39;Hand tools Risk Assessment&#39; as applicable.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>2</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>1</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="3">
      <my:Description>Trapped fingers, toes</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>2</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>4</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) When opening manhole, suitable lifting tools should be used; 
b) Finger should not be used to lift / hold the edges; 
c) Fingers should not be used to align holes in machinery being mounted; 
d) Consult `Manual Handling Risk Assessment`; 
e) Consult `Heavy Parts Handling `Risk Assessment.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>2</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>2</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="4">
      <my:Description>Electricity</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>3</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Consult `Maintenance/Repair of Electrical Equipment `Risk Assessment; 
b) Switch off power for Pump and Blower when maintenance; 
c) &quot;Do Not Switch On&quot; Warning Poster to be posted to prevent accidental starting the unit.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="5">
      <my:Description>Hazardous substances, including biological hazards</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>2</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>4</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>Consult `Dealing With Hazardous Substances` Risk Assessment.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>2</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>2</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
    <my:Hazard my:HazardId="6">
      <my:Description>Moving Parts</my:Description>
      <my:Severity>3</my:Severity>
      <my:Likelihood>3</my:Likelihood>
      <my:RiskFactor>5</my:RiskFactor>
      <my:ControlMeasures>a) Before any maintenance/repair commences the Manufacturer`s manual must be consulted; 
b) Permission to carry out the job from Chief Engineer must be obtained; 
c) Safe Work Permit to be issued; 
d) Crew engaged in the task to be instructed and briefed.</my:ControlMeasures>
      <my:ReducedSeverity>3</my:ReducedSeverity>
      <my:ReducedLikelihood>1</my:ReducedLikelihood>
      <my:ReducedRiskFactor>3</my:ReducedRiskFactor>
    </my:Hazard>
  </my:Hazards>
